@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

   @{b}Introduction@{ub}
  --------------

   VBRControl increases the system speed by moving  the  processor  vector
   base from chipmem into fastmem.

   There are several programs doing the same job, but there not very  save
   and even may crash when changing the VBR.

@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"

   @{b}System requirements@{ub}
  ---------------------

   VBRControl (should work) works on all Amigas with OS 2.0 or higher  and
   an  680x0  processor,  where x>0! Or easily: VBRControl isn´t woring on
   MC68000, but on all other 68K systems.
@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Features"

   @{b}Features@{ub}
  ----------

  ° 100% Assembler

@endnode
@node "Distribution" "Distribution"

   @{b}Distribution@{ub}
  --------------

   This program should be published on every public medium, as long as all
   files  in  the archive are unchanged. If this medium is a CD I expect a
   free copy. (AminetCDs excluded)

   @{b}VBRControl is Mailware.@{ub}

   I expect from everybody, who uses VBRControl regularly, to send  me  an
   email  or postcard. I think this does not hurt anybody, and I will have
   more fun to integrate new features.

   @{b}I am not liable for injures or data loss caused by VBRControl! The  use
   of VBRControl is on your own responsibility !!!@{ub}

@endnode
@node "HowToInstall" "How to install VBRControl"

   @{b}How to install VBRControl@{ub}
  ---------------------------

   Just copy VBRControl into your C: drawer and add the following line  to
   your user-startup:

   VBRControl ON QUIET

   Thats all!

@endnode
